            "text": "Pandemics have a profound impact on our world ,",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "causing loss of life ,",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "affecting our culture",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "and historically shaping our genetics . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "The response to a pandemic requires both resilience and imagination . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "It has been clearly documented that obtaining an accurate estimate and trends of the actual infection rate and mortality risk are very important for policy makers and medical professionals . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "One can not estimate mortality rates",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "without an accurate assessment of the number of infected individuals in the population . <S>",
            "relation": "CONDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "This need is also aligned with identifying the infected individuals",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "so they can be properly treated ,",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "monitored",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "and tracked . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "However , accurate estimation of the infection rate , locally , geographically and nationally is important independently . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "These infection rate estimates can guide policy makers at both state , national or world level to achieve a better management of risk to society . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "The decisions",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "facing policy makers",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "are very different during early stages of an emerging epidemic",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "where the infection rate is low ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 19,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "middle stages",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 20,
            "parent": 19,
            "text": "where the rate is rapidly climbing ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 21,
            "parent": 19,
            "text": "and later stages",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 22,
            "parent": 21,
            "text": "where the epidemic curve has flattened to a low and relatively sustainable rate . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 23,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "In this paper we provide relatively efficient pooling methods",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 24,
            "parent": 23,
            "text": "to both estimate infection rates",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 25,
            "parent": 24,
            "text": "and identify infected individuals for populations with low infection rates . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 26,
            "parent": 24,
            "text": "These estimates may provide significant cost reductions",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 27,
            "parent": 26,
            "text": "for testing in rural communities , third world countries and other situations",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 28,
            "parent": 27,
            "text": "where the cost of testing is expensive",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 29,
            "parent": 28,
            "text": "or testing is not widely available . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
